
We are given root of the binary tree and our job is to extract the leaf nodes as list of list until root != null.
Input: root = [1,2,3,4,5]
Output: [[4,5,3],[2],[1]]


what solution does :

while root is not null:
    collect current leaves
    remove those leaves from the tree
    add collected leaves to result

Example :
        1
       / \
      2   3
     / \
    4   5

    first round leaf nodes are [4, 5, 3]

    then tree will be  1
                      /
                    2
      Now second round will be: leaves = [2] , result = [ [4,5,3], [2]]
    Now Tree will become : 1

    then third round of iteration : leaves = [1], result  = [ [4,5,3] [2], [1]]

    
class Solution {
    public List<List<Integer>> findLeaves(TreeNode root) {

        List<List<Integer>> result = new ArrayList<>();

        while(root != null)
        {
            List<Integer> leaves = new ArrayList<>();
            root = removeLeaves(root, leaves);
            result.add(leaves);
        }
        
        return result;
    }

    private TreeNode removeLeaves(TreeNode root, List<Integer> leaves)
    {
        if(root == null){ return null; }

        if(root.left == null && root.right == null)
        {
            leaves.add(root.val);
            return null;
        }

        root.left = removeLeaves(root.left, leaves);
        root.right = removeLeaves(root.right, leaves);


        return root;

    }
}
